In England, in the seven days to 14 October, there were 246,661 new confirmed cases (436.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 07 October, there were 202,285 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 22% (44,376 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 19 October is 7,262,958 (12,843.4 cases per 100,000 population).
